			Text		Use the "Show My Temp Tables" button to see what tables you
					 have stored under your UserID. You will see a list of your
					 tables along with a timestamp of when each was created.    
					 If you want to delete a table, click the "Delete My Temp
					 Table" button (you can only delete 1 at a time). A prompt
					 will appear asking you for the name of the table to delete.
					 Type the name between curly braces and click "ok".
					 (Example: to delete a table called "Test" you would type
					 {Test}.) If the delete was successful you will either get a
					 "no data returned" or "invalid cursor state" message,
					 otherwise you will get an error message. If you are unsure
					 whether or not the delete worked, click the "Show My Temp
					 Tables" button to see if the table is still listed.
